PREAMBLE

This software was made by a citizen of Gwangmyeong, Gyeonggi-do, South Korea.
It was built with generative AI tools, because the author loves open source
and loves the city where they live.

Nobody asked for this. No government funded it. A local resident simply thought,
"Our city hall officers deserve a decent AI tool too" — one that's free, keeps
data private, and runs right on the officer's own PC. Even in isolated government
networks that can't benefit from cloud AI, officers should still get help. So
the author built one.

The GM-Social License follows the open-source philosophy: use it freely, take
it apart, fix it, share it. But there's one condition you won't find in any
other license — Social Gratitude. When you start using this software for real,
take a moment to learn about Gwangmyeong. Then tell the world about it.
That's the only price.


