          - Any format works: blog post, social media, credits page in your
            app, article — your choice
          - Include at least one of these hashtags:
            #Gwangmyeong #광명 #광명시 #GM_AI_Hub

    (b) DISCOVER GWANGMYEONG (광명 발견하기)

        Share a place, landmark, neighborhood, or story from Gwangmyeong on
        at least THREE (3) different social media platforms.

        This is not marketing. It's discovery. We're asking you to get to
        know a real city.

        Things you could post:
          - Gwangmyeong Cave (광명동굴) — a former gold mine turned into a
            cultural space
          - Something you ate at Gwangmyeong Traditional Market (광명전통시장)
          - Gwangmyeong Upcycle Art Center (광명업사이클아트센터)
          - A photo from a walk along Anyang Stream (안양천 산책로)
          - The neighborhoods: Cheolsan (철산동), Soha (소하동), Haan (하안동)
          - A cafe, a park, an alley, a sky in Gwangmyeong
          - Something you learned about the city
          - Even a single map pin or one line of thought is enough

        Every post must include at least TWO (2) of these hashtags:
          #Gwangmyeong #광명 #광명시 #DiscoverGwangmyeong
          #경기도 #GyeonggiDo #GM_AI_Hub #OpenSourceKorea

        Any public platform counts:
          Instagram, X (Twitter), Facebook, YouTube, LinkedIn, TikTok,
          Naver Blog, KakaoStory, Threads, Mastodon, Medium, Brunch,
          Reddit, etc.

    (c) PROOF OF GRATITUDE (Nice to do, not required)

        Open an issue on the project repo or add your name to GRATITUDE.md
        via pull request. The community will be happy to see it.

    WHY THIS CONDITION EXISTS:

    Gwangmyeong is not Seoul. It's not a famous tech hub or startup city.
    It's a small city of about 200,000 people in Gyeonggi-do.

    But Gwangmyeong's dedicated public officers work incredibly hard for
    their citizens. It was frustrating to see them left out of the AI
    revolution.

    As a startup founder who uses AI in many ways, the author wanted to
    share that experience and help — not as a contractor, but as a neighbor.

    When this software spreads to other cities and countries, we hope the
    name Gwangmyeong travels with it. Not money, but attention. Not a
    contract, but a kind word. A moment of curiosity about a city most of
    the world has never heard of — that's enough.

